doc: The collection of constraints to be used as starting point for the interpolation.
The collection of constraints to be used as ending point for the interpolation.

Controls the factor lambda to be used for the interpolation: final_value = initial_value + lambda * (final_value - initial_value). If the given string is parsable to a double, then it is used as the value of lambda. Otherwise, the string is interpreted as a expression defining the value of lambda (e.g., '${sin(0.2)}' would be evaluated to the value of the sine of 0.2).

tag: the importing of chemical objects (e.g., molecular geometries)
